venue.name: Hong Lim Market & Food Centre 芳林巴刹与熟食中心 (Hong Lim Complex Market & Food Centre)

tips.text: Best fish soup found here!
Wide range of yogurt! If u are looking for something healthy and a fast meal. Here it is! Nice and cozy place. Only down side is the food here is abit pricy.

venue.name: Dong Fang Mei Shi Fan Dian 东方美食饭店

tips.text: 辣子鸡，金针菇拌黄瓜丝，蒜泥白肉，水煮牛肉

venue.name: Si Wei Mao Cai 思味冒菜

formattedAddress: 33 Mosque St (btw South Bridge Rd. & New Bridge Rd.)
location.crossStreet: btw South Bridge Rd. & New Bridge Rd.

tips.text: Their 花仁豆腐 is the best & unique.
Brown rice salad with some chicken and assorted veggies is good here. Really healthy options, but nice big portions also.
Fantastic food; terrible service 😡 Served by a hovering waitress who asked "Are you done with that?" and "Can you finish that so I can clear the table?" We left within 75 minutes of being seated.

formattedAddress: #01-12, Lau Pa Sat Festival Market (18 Raffles Quay)

tips.text: Have never paid this much for thunder tea rice 💸💸💸💸💸
Keep a stack of menus at your desk at work - makes it easy to grab lunch for pals (or send them off with an order for you!)
Here is the menu!
Every single thing we ordered was superb. Reasonably price too
Great bar - amazing ginger beer - get a seat in the dinning room at the bar
Hearts the beef vindaloo and aloo gobi.

venue.name: Imperial Treasure Super Peking Duck Restaurant 御寶至尊烤鴨店

tips.text: Duck of course. Not as crowded as the Paragon branch.
Must try: oriental salad, drunken chicken, duck in onion pastry, fried pork chop noodle or fried rice and of course the xiao long bao!
Best french bakery in Singapore. Actually, best bakery period.
Duck confit was the best we've had in Singapore. Crispy & fragrant, every bite was pleasurable. And there's that sinful side of potato crisp fried in duck fat. Ahhh...
Come on Sunday.. Not many people and enjoy the meal. Thumbs up!!
The Awesome Salad is truly awesome: a generous serving of smoked salmon, duck rillettes, salami, chicken breast and avocado on a bed of greens, with a side of pesto panini
Sooooo gooood
Yummy chocolate tart:)
Love the ambience and deco of the restaurant. The food is marvelous too. Shall go back again and again and again. Cheers.

venue.name: Song Fa Bak Kut Teh 松發肉骨茶

tips.text: The food here was great. However, the management should relook at the queuing system as there are two queues – one at each entrance.
Happy hours daily till 8pm 25% off!
A cold atmosphere. But good coffee & food. Wish they had a menu. It's tiring just listening to the waitress reciting it & I'm pretty sure it's tiring for them to recite it too...
Food was only average for the pricing which will set you back at least $50++ /pax. Claimed 20% birthday discount but cashier unaware. Overall not worthy of the price.

venue.name: Xiu Ji Ikan Bilis Yong Tau Fu

formattedAddress: #02-87/88, Chinatown Complex Market & Food Centre (355 Smith Street)

tips.text: The ikan billis or deep fried anchovies are delicious.
Get the kaisendon and una tamago
Must try their beef bulgogi & steamed egg!
Good Indian food. They have dum biriyani as well.
Staff were extremely friendly and helpful ! The spaces are big in size and have all the proper appliances!

Amazing Concept! An Izakaya-ModernTapas Bar with a suprising menu changing everyday. Tasted Gurnard Tartar with Quinoa&Tofu and Kampong Egg with Baby Satong and Chorizo. Awesome flavours and textures!
party of 5 could not finish tomahawk wagyu. brought giant bone home for flintstones cosplay. bam bam! uni pasta = good but karaage and cold truffle potato = average.

venue.name: Tian Tian Hainanese Chicken Rice 天天海南鸡饭

formattedAddress: Stall 10, Maxwell Food Centre (1 Kadayanallur St.)

tips.text: Too oily
Yellow Noodles with lots of Lard, Pork Jelly/Meat Ball/HaoCho Platter, Braised Goose Webs, Bamboo Shoots, Pomfret Porridge, Oyster Omelette, Mutton Stew, Crispy Bee Hoon, Chestnut Pancake, Tau Suan
Make sure you ask for the free coffe if spend over $10.00
The buffet is really value for money. My Favourite is the brisket even though the fat content is so high. Eat with raw garlic and kimchi, chased with cold beer. It's so so good.
Check out the CitiBank Menu...
紅燒肉 (Red-Cooked Pork), 紫蘇黃瓜 (Fried Cucumber)， 手撕包菜 (Stir-Fried Cabbage)，鹹蛋黃茄子(Eggplant Fingers w Salted-Egg Crust) are all splendid.
This is likely one of the most overrated places in Singapore; mostly by expats. It's expensive and every piece of sushi has frozen crab meat filler.
This is one of the best kept secrets in Singapore, they have a great champagne selection and one the best cold cuts and cheese platters in town.

formattedAddress: #B2-05/06, Marina Bay Link Mall (8A Marina Boulevard)

tips.text: Be there before 11:30am during weekdays to secure a seat fast.

formattedAddress: PARKROYAL on Pickering (3 Upper Pickering St.)

tips.text: Don't forget to try the Lime Bar. Delicious bar bites and a great club sandwich: The William.... In-or outside if the AC is too cold....

venue.name: Hong Kong Soya Sauce Chicken Rice & Noodle

formattedAddress: #02-126, Chinatown Complex Market & Food Centre (335 Smith St)

tips.text: You have to eat here at least once if you are near the china town. but beware for a long queue when lunch time. taste soooo good and cheap as well.
Excellent sushi and great service. Trust the chef, it will be delicious. 🍣
Sashimi rice bowl was yum!

formattedAddress: #02-129, Amoy Street Food Centre (7 Maxwell Road)

tips.text: Long queue but its worth it. $5 for small, $6 for medium and $7 for big size. Absolutely delicious! I would certainly recommend this to anyone especially food lovers!

tips.text: Best sausage! Try Smoked Pork with Cheese!
